Package Monopoly

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Card
    The Card class provides a container to hold data about Chance and Community Chest cards, and allows for operations on to be done on a Player object.
    ChanceTile
    The ChanceTile class is a vestigial subclass of Tile.
    CommunityChestTile
    The CommunityChestTile class is a vestigial subclass of Tile.
    Dice
    The Dice class allows for realistic random dice rolls.
    FreeParkingTile
    The FreeParkingTile class is a subclass of Tile.
    GoTile
    The GoTile class is an extension of Tile, with no internal differences in functionality
    GoToJailTile
    The GoToJail class is an extension of Tile, with no internal differences in functionality
    JailTile
    The JailTile class is an extension of Tile, with no internal differences in functionality
    MonopolyGame
    The MonopolyGame class is responsible for handling all functions of an instance of a Monopoly game.
    OwnableTile  
    Player
    A monopoly Player class which provides features for managing a players balance, smartly evading bankruptcy, managing properties/assets, using get out of jail free cards, tracking their turns in jail, knowing their position on the board.
    PropertyTile
    The PropertyTile is an subclass of Tile.
    RailroadTile
    The RailRoad class is an extension of Tile, with a unique algorithm to get rent based on ownership of other railroads
    TaxTile
    The TaxTile class is an extension of Tile, with no internal differences in functionality
    Tile
    The Tile class is the superclass for all the squares on a Monopoly game board.
    TradeBroker
    The TradeBroker class, when implemented, allows for automated players to create trade offers, accept offers, deny offers, etc
    TradeOffer  
    UtilityTile
    The UtilityTile class is a subclass of Tile which has specific algorithms for getting rent amounts.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Tile.TileType
    Enumeration used to express the type of tile the current *Tile object refers to
